<LanguageData>
  
  <!-- EN: Initial approach book-Earth element -->
  <RI_Book_EarthElement.label>土行法门书《乾坤经》</RI_Book_EarthElement.label>
  <!-- EN: An ancient book made of Qi condensation, the title of which is "Qian Kun".\n\nStrength born of accumulation, heaven and earth as its burden. Earth cultivation is the art of resonating with the land itself. Qi sinks like roots into the soil; walking, standing, and resting are all forms of practice. As a result, most Earth cultivators do not rely on their senses to perceive the world, but instead link themselves to the ground, refining Earth Columns to serve as anchors through which their techniques are realized.Those of profound attainment can draw the power of Kun Earth into their bodies, stir the deep earth veins, and carve out a world of their own.\n\nWarning: Once a cultivator fully comprehends a tome of a given path, they become bound to its teachings and can no longer pursue any other cultivation method! -->
  <RI_Book_EarthElement.description>一本由灵气凝聚而成的古书，书名写着《乾坤经》。厚积薄发，乾坤承载。土行法门，修炼的是与大地的共鸣，灵气如根扎地，行走坐卧皆是修行。这使得大部分土行修士，并不依赖感官来判断，而是通过链接土地，提炼乾元柱，来达成各种目标。修为高深者，可引坤土之力加身，引动地脉震荡，开辟自身一方世界。\n\n注意：一旦完全钻研完一本法门书，修炼者将与这条法门绑定，无法再学习其他法门！</RI_Book_EarthElement.description>
  <!-- EN: After reading {PARENT_label}, the cultivator{STUDIER_labelShort} takes the Earth element Initial approach as his cultivation direction! -->
  <RI_Book_EarthElement.comps.CompBookStudiable.completedLetterText>阅读了{PARENT_label}后, 修炼者{STUDIER_labelShort}将土行法门作为了自己的修炼方向！</RI_Book_EarthElement.comps.CompBookStudiable.completedLetterText>
  <!-- EN: {PARENT_label} becomes some dirt and disappears. -->
  <RI_Book_EarthElement.comps.CompBookStudiable.completedLetterTitle>{PARENT_label}化为一捧尘土，消散了。</RI_Book_EarthElement.comps.CompBookStudiable.completedLetterTitle>
  
  <!-- EN: Initial approach book-Fire element -->
  <RI_Book_FireElement.label>火行法门书《离火诀》</RI_Book_FireElement.label>
  <!-- EN: An ancient book made of Qi condensation, the title of which is "Art of Flame".\n\nThe Fire Method is fierce in nature—unyielding, ever-burning, its force both violent and resolute. Yet, at its core, it is intertwined with the vitality of Yang, a fusion of destruction and renewal. Those who walk this path temper their hearts in flame, where spiritual energy serves as kindling, and Heartfire blazes unceasingly.\n\nUpon initiation, the Heartfire stirs one’s nature, causing restlessness and emotional turmoil. One’s temperament wavers, unstable as flickering embers. Yet this trial must be overcome, for only those who master their inner fire may grasp the true essence of the Departing Flame. In the end, those who reach the pinnacle of this path can ignite the Heartfire within others, reducing all illusions to ashes.\n\nWarning: Once a cultivator fully comprehends a tome of a given path, they become bound to its teachings and can no longer pursue any other cultivation method! -->
  <RI_Book_FireElement.description>一本由灵气凝聚而成的古书，书名写着《离火诀》。\n\n火行法门，个性炽烈；焚而不息；刚猛强烈，与阳刚生机交织难分。火行修炼者炼的是心，灵气为薪柴，心火熊燃。\n\n入门时，心火会撩拨人性，令人心烦意乱，性情不定，但这是必须突破的一关，只有驾驭心火之人，方能掌控离火大道。最终，境界大成者，更能引燃他人的心火，焚尽虚妄。\n\n注意：一旦完全钻研完一本法门书，修炼者将与这条法门绑定，无法再学习其他法门！</RI_Book_FireElement.description>
  <!-- EN: After reading {PARENT_label}, the cultivator{STUDIER_labelShort} takes the Fire element Initial approach as his cultivation direction! -->
  <RI_Book_FireElement.comps.CompBookStudiable.completedLetterText>阅读了{PARENT_label}后, 修炼者{STUDIER_labelShort}将火行法门作为了自己的修炼方向！</RI_Book_FireElement.comps.CompBookStudiable.completedLetterText>
  <!-- EN: {PARENT_label} becomes some sparks of Qi and disappears. -->
  <RI_Book_FireElement.comps.CompBookStudiable.completedLetterTitle>{PARENT_label}化为点点火光，消散了。</RI_Book_FireElement.comps.CompBookStudiable.completedLetterTitle>
  
  <!-- EN: Initial approach book-Wood element -->
  <RI_Book_WoodElement.label>木行法门书《巽木残卷》</RI_Book_WoodElement.label>
  <!-- EN: An ancient book made of Qi condensation, the title of which is "Incomplete scroll of Xun wood".\n\nThe Wood Path Method is a cultivation technique focused on the power of vitality. Cultivator of the Wood Path perceive the flowing vitality within plants and trees and learn to manipulate it. Those who attain mastery can refine this vitality within their own core, strengthening their blood and nourishing their spirit.\n\nThe Five Elements Sect was once the foremost sect in the cultivation world. Its Wood Path division had the power to freely command life force, creating wondrous flowers and magical trees, and enjoying unmatched prestige. However, after a devastating sect war, the Wood Path became the target of the other four elemental branches. In the end, to ensure the survival of a few disciples, the Wood Path was sealed away and its teachings voluntarily abolished.\n\nWarning: Once a cultivator fully comprehends a tome of a given path, they become bound to its teachings and can no longer pursue any other cultivation method! -->
  <RI_Book_WoodElement.description>一本由灵气凝聚而成的古书，书名写着《巽木残卷》。\n\n木行法门，修炼生机之术。木行修炼者感悟草木之中流动的生机，对其进行操纵，大成者可将生机化于自生丹田，壮血气，益元神。\n\n五行宗曾是修仙界第一门派，其木行分支可随意调配生机，制造奇花灵木，风光无限。然而门派战争后，木行遭到其余四行针对，最终以自废法门的方式为少量后人换来生存的机会。\n\n注意：一旦完全钻研完一本法门书，修炼者将与这条法门绑定，无法再学习其他法门！</RI_Book_WoodElement.description>
  <!-- EN: After reading {PARENT_label}, the cultivator{STUDIER_labelShort} takes the Wood element Initial approach as his cultivation direction! -->
  <RI_Book_WoodElement.comps.CompBookStudiable.completedLetterText>阅读了{PARENT_label}后, 修炼者{STUDIER_labelShort}将木行法门作为了自己的修炼方向！</RI_Book_WoodElement.comps.CompBookStudiable.completedLetterText>
  <!-- EN: {PARENT_label} becomes some sparks of Qi and disappears. -->
  <RI_Book_WoodElement.comps.CompBookStudiable.completedLetterTitle>{PARENT_label}化为片片绿叶，消散了。</RI_Book_WoodElement.comps.CompBookStudiable.completedLetterTitle>
  
</LanguageData>